[SN]TITLE[SN]
PE teacher guilty of sexually touching teenage girl

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A PE teacher has been found guilty of sexual activity with a 15-year-old girl.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Richard Maycock, who taught at a school in Coventry, denied inappropriately touching the girl in a disabled toilet.
The girl told police the 44-year-old said she would get into trouble if she told anyone. He will be sentenced at Coventry Crown Court next month.
He had previously admitted to two counts of sexual activity with a child.
The court heard tried to remove a piece of clothing from the girl and then inappropriately touched her.
In police interviews played to the jury on Monday, the girl said she was scared.
